To meet the rapid business expansion, we are looking for an additional new headcount of the QS talents to join our QS team. You will involve the entire tender management from evaluation to arrive the bid decisions and the cost management.   

What we look for?

Execute the cost estimation, cost control and analysis to reach the cost efficiency;
Pricing and estimate the cost of different material needed for the E&M projects;
Responsible for the tender analysis & risk assessment and provide effective solution;
Prepare and ensure tender documents and technical documentations are properly; complied with company policy and standard for tender document submission;
Liaise with clients, or main contractors, or sub-contractors, or government regularly on tender documents, and attend tender meetings;
Deliver the final account settlement;
Coordinate and communicate with internal or external stakeholders.

What you need to succeed?

Higher Diploma/ Degree holder in Quantity Surveying, Engineering or Building Services Engineering;
At least 4 years’ relevant experience in E&M or Building Services industry;
Experience in tendering, budgeting and cost control management is an advantage;
Strong analytical mind, independent and a proactive team player;
Good command of both written and spoken in Chinese and English.

What we offer?

Stable and friendly work environment
Open office design
Annual leave
Medical insurance
Education subsidy
Year-end double pay
Discretionary bonus
Excellent career development
Unlimited beverages and snacks
Internal and external training programme
On-job training

Interested parties, please send your detailed resume with expected salary via “Apply Now” for our consideration

Responsibilities:


Handling data center infrastructure design & technical support for projects, in-house design co-ordination and administration;
Preparation of tender documentation, system specification and drawings;
Participate in electrical system design & process;
Provide on-site technical support and verification, T&C etc.;
Prepare feasibility report, design proposal, budgetary estimation, electrical design calculation, and tender bidding document for E&M projects.
Other relevant assignments as specified by managers.

 Requirements:


Diploma / Higher Diploma / Degree or above in Electrical Engineering or related disciplines;
3-5 years' solid experience in consulting firm / electrical contracting company;
Experience in infrastructure design, such as, HV, LV, ELV, Genset system, UPS system, discrimination study etc.
Proficient in MS Office, Sketchup, AutoCAD or BIM, luminaire calculation software knowledge is preferable;
Holder of relevant electrical license and with knowledge of using BIM & CFD will be an advantage;
Able to work with tight schedules;
Self-motivated, self-disciplined, organized, detail-oriented and responsible;
Good communication, interpersonal and problem-solving skills;
An attractive remuneration package and fringe benefits will be offered to the right candidate. Interested parties, please send your resume stating with current and expected salary to the Human Resources Department by clicking Apply Now.


For more information, please visit the corporate website at www.newtechapac.com

All information collected will be kept strictly confidential and for recruitment purpose only.

Responsibilities:

Assist Director to evaluate market research data and develop integrate business analysis for Group Strategic business decision, ESG and sustainability initiatives;
Conduct research and identify market trends and potential investment / new business opportunities;
Manage analysis projects including planning, execution, reports and presentation to Directors Office;
Communicate with business partners to smoothen the research and analysis projects;
Keep track of market trend and competitors’ activities;
Project document administration;

Requirements:

University real estate / sustainability studies / Environmental Science or related discipline;
2-5 years of market research experiences who should have strong analytical skills with experience in conducting reports and presentation.
Strong project management skills and attention to detail;

We offer competitive remuneration package to the right candidates. Interested parties, please submit your resume (in both English and Chinese), with stating current and expected salary, availability, contact phone number by APPLY NOW.

All applications and personal information collected will be treated in strict confidence and only be used for the purpose of recruitment and selection. The information collected will be accessed by our authorized personnel only. Unsuccessful applications will be retained for six months of possible future job matching, and will be destroyed after the expiry of six months.

