We are looking for a professional, energetic and experienced engineer to join.  Reporting to the Senior Project Engineer/ Project Manager, the candidate will be an active member of a project management team which develops and executes a mega engineering project.  Major duties will include:

Responsibilities

Ensure that Company Safety, Health, Environmental and Quality framework is incorporated in all aspects of the Project’s development and implementation;
Perform Electrical system quality inspection activities in accordance with the Project Quality Plan;
Keep Construction Superintendent / Deputy Construction Superintendent updated with status of Electrical system quality issues and alert any potential quality problems in advance;
Perform witness inspections and monitor production processes;
Monitor the quality and workmanship of the E&M works to ensure compliance with the contract drawings, specifications and other standards;
Monitor the work progress and proactively anticipate interface and construction problems to ensure timely delivery and completion;
Review, evaluate and endorse Contractor's and Suppliers’ completion files and records and ensure related accuracy and adequacy;
Witness acceptance tests and perform final quality check against design requirement, specification and acceptance criteria prior to acceptance of E&M works, as appropriate;
Provide expertise to site team to avoid/resolve quality problems;
Monitor Suppliers’ and Contractor’s quality assurance and quality control activities.

Requirements:

Higher Diploma in Electrical related discipline or equivalent with at least 7 years of site construction experience; or a recognized degree in Electrical related discipline with at least 5 years relevant experience; plus 2 years minimum recent experience in E&M, Instrumentation & Control system hook-up, commissioning and start-up experience;
Hong Kong Registered Electrical Worker Grade H;
Possession of Certificate for Construction Safety Supervisors would be an advantage;
Experience related to project scope, or related offshore project inspection experience or minimum 2 years’ recent experience in E&M inspection, equipment mechanical completion, Factory Acceptance Test, functional loop check would be an advantage;
Possess knowledge of measurement instrumentation, Pneumatic/Hydraulic actuators, Distributed Control System/ Programmable Logic Controllers and Telecommunication system installation standard and testing requirement;
Basic understanding on explosion proof equipment installation;
Good communication and interpersonal skills to work with different stakeholders;
Able to work independently and under pressure;
Willing to work under the offshore marine condition and work under shifts;
Excellent in the use of MS Office applications, including Word, Excel and PowerPoint. Experience in using company systems would be advantage;
Good written and spoken English and/ or Chinese. Proficient in Mandarin would be preferable.

We offer successful candidates a remuneration package, comprehensive benefit package and excellent career prospects. Interested parties please send your resume in details with last/current and expected salary by clicking “Apply Now”.

