We are expanding our research and development team in Hong Kong to research, develop, enhance and implement our innovative solutions for multiple industry/sector leaders. We are looking for a proactive and energetic candidate to join our R&D team. Since we are introducing a series of disruptive products to the market, we offer a unique opportunity for our colleagues to grow with us quickly and explore multiple disciplines in addition to cloud software development.

The incumbent of this role will deliver a scalable, innovative, high available software to support IoT applications, collaboration in line with the business strategy.

Job Duties

Develop A.I. algorithms for Cloud severs and AIoT products;
Participate in product requirement collection, feasibility studies, system design and tender submissions.
Design and implement software for IoT/AIoT products;
Conduct software test & commissioning and systems validation & verifications of the works in compliance to the project requirement;
Liaise with the information security team to ensure security, reliability integrity and robustness of solution design;
Provide updates related to cloud infrastructure and platform technology.

Requirements

Master or Bachelor Degree holder in Engineering, Computer Science, Business or equivalent;
At least 5 years of experience in embedded system and software development in C/C+;
Proficiency in Linux.
Experience in AWS or IoT sensors or embedded system is a plus.
At least 2 years of working experience in AWS or IoT sensors is plus;
Proficient in both verbal and written English & Chinese (Cantonese & Mandarin);
Strong communication, interpersonal and presentation skills with the ability to communicate in both verbal and written English and Chinese;
Leadership and people management skills will be advantageous; 
Ability to work independently and innovatively with good technical, analytical and problem-solving skill.

We offer attractive remuneration package including 5-day work, flexible work hours and other benefits to the right candidates. Interested parties please forward cover letter and full resume with expected salary and quote job reference number to

VTech Group of Companies, 
The Human Resources and Administration Department, 
23/F, Block 1, Tai Ping Industrial Centre,
57 Ting Kok Road, Tai Po, Hong Kong

OR apply on-line directly through our corporate website at www.vtech.com/en/careers/   

For more information about us, please visit our website at www.vtech.com   

All applications will be used for the purpose of recruitment only. Applicants not invited for interview within 4 weeks may consider their applications unsuccessful. We will retain the applications for a maximum period of six months and may refer them to suitable openings within our Group.

Responsibilities:

Assist Associate Director in the formulation of marketing, branding and visitor experience enhancement strategies through a series of architectural and interior design and implementation processes with integration of smart technologies and arts;
Coordinate with a wide spectrum of stakeholders such as HKSTP departments (Marketing Team, Clusters, Facility Management Team, Project Team etc,), external strategic partners, consultants, contractors, etc. on the implementation and delivery of the approved strategies on upgrading works at the Spine, MICE venues, F&B, Tenants’ Showcase plus strengthening of various spatial connections and landscape attractions and other related matters;
Prepare presentation materials and progress reports for internal and external stakeholders;
Handle various requests and matters initiated by F&B/MICE operators and users;
Liaise with F&B tenants and review their design submissions for incorporation into the tenancy agreement as well as monitor tenant’s implementation works to safeguard HKSTP brand standard; and
Perform any other duties as assigned by supervisor.

Requirements:

A recognized degree or above in Architecture, Interior Design, or relevant disciplines with at least three years of relevant experience OR an Associate Degree/ a Higher Diploma with substantial years of relevant experience will also be considered;
Solid experience in design and project management in development and/or A&A projects in similar scale and nature is preferred;
Exposure in global F&B scenes and their interiors lifestyle trending;
Good understanding of local regulations on both building and licensing authorities;
Excellent skills in using 2D and 3D computer softwares for preparing graphical presentation materials;  
Passionate in art and culture, a team player with strong interpersonal and communication skills, self-motivated, confident, creative and strong desire to achieve better performance; and
Proficient in both written and spoken English and Chinese.

We offer market competitive compensation, 5-day work week, and generous benefits including medical and life insurance; and voluntary contribution in addition to the legal minimum MPF.  To apply, please send your full resume with current and expected salary to the Human Resources & Office Administration Department, Hong Kong Science and Technology Parks Corporation, 5/F, Building 5E, 5 Science Park East Avenue, Hong Kong Science Park, Hong Kong or, by email via "Apply Now" on or before 27 January 2022.   Please quote the reference number on the email subject/envelope and the application letter. 

Personal data provided will be treated in strict confidence and used for recruitment purpose only.  All personal data collected will be used strictly in accordance with employer’s personal data policies, you can access to HKSTP’s Personal Information Collection Statement at https://www.hkstp.org/hkstp_web/en/hkstp/personal-information-collection-statement-recruitment

Applicants not invited for interview within four weeks after application deadline may consider their applications unsuccessful.  Personal data of unsuccessful applicants will be retained for a maximum of two years. 

