Reporting to the Strategy and New Project Lead, the appointee will be required to:

take a vital role of managing the project of setting up a new satellite sustainability-focused laboratory in Hong Kong (https://www.theopenlab.one/);
oversee all the activities involved and progress of work, ensuring an on-schedule and smooth commencement of the new lab;
manage the development of the lab including the involvement in the design stage, tender/award, construction, safety standards;
build and lead project teams comprising of external consultants, contractors and suppliers as well as internal cross-divisional groups;
manage and control the budget;
undergo other project administrative tasks, such as procurement, fund application, regular progress reporting;
work closely with Research, Business Development and Marketing team to coordinate project and new initiatives related the lab; and
perform any other duties as assigned.

Requirements:

A bachelor’s degree or above in a Construction Management / Architecture / Engineering or related disciplines;
5 or more years of relevant work experience. Experience in industrial, lab management or lab operation would be an advantage but not a must;
With solid project management and people management skills, PMP/CAPM certification is a plus;
Conversant with government procedures and regulations is a plus;
Strong sense of project ownership and proactive working attitude;
Excellent planning and organizing skills;
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills;
Highly-organized and capable of working under pressure with multi-task assignments; and
Fluent in written and spoken English, with good command of Putonghua being an advantage.
Applicants should state their current and expected salary in the application. Salary offered will be commensurate with qualifications and experience. Appointment will be offered on a contract basis, re-engagement thereafter is subject to mutual agreement.


Applicants are invited to send detailed curriculum vitae in strict confidence to Human Resources Manager, HKRITA, R906-8, Shirley Chan Building, The Hong Kong Polytechnic University, Hung Hom, Kowloon. Recruitment will continue until the position is filled. HKRITA reserves the right to consider late applications and nominations, and to fill or not to fill the positions. Personal data provided by applicants will be used for recruitment and other employment-related purpose.

